Gamemaker Zynga Close to Raising $500 Million, WSJ Reports

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-02-18T05:55:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/gamemaker-zynga-close-to-raising-500-million-wsj-reports.html
Zynga Inc., which makes games such
as FarmVille and CityVille for Facebook Inc., is close to
raising $500 million in financing, the Wall Street Journal
reported, citing people familiar with the matter.  Zynga is in talks with T. Rowe Price Group Inc., Fidelity
Investments and  Morgan Stanley , and money raised is likely to be
based on a company value of $10 billion, the newspaper said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Peterson at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  